      "content": "i feel like i'm just overreacting because of the stress i've been under lately. the drooping is very slight and it's gone if i flex my face hard. the pressure is the main thing. if i just take a double dose of the sumatriptan right now to knock it out fast, wouldn't that be better than sitting in a hospital for 8 hours for nothing? just tell me if that's a safe combo for a bad attack.",
